737 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3 && __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_ASCII
738 static int __Pyx_sys_getdefaultencoding_not_ascii;
739 static int __Pyx_init_sys_getdefaultencoding_params(void) {
740  PyObject* sys;
741  PyObject* default_encoding = NULL;
742  PyObject* ascii_chars_u = NULL;
743  PyObject* ascii_chars_b = NULL;
744  const char* default_encoding_c;
745  sys = PyImport_ImportModule("sys");
746  if (!sys) goto bad;
747  default_encoding = PyObject_CallMethod(sys, (char*) "getdefaultencoding", NULL);
748  Py_DECREF(sys);
749  if (!default_encoding) goto bad;
750  default_encoding_c = PyBytes_AsString(default_encoding);
751  if (!default_encoding_c) goto bad;
752  if (strcmp(default_encoding_c, "ascii") == 0) {
753  __Pyx_sys_getdefaultencoding_not_ascii = 0;
754  } else {
755  char ascii_chars[128];
756  int c;
757  for (c = 0; c < 128; c++) {
758  ascii_chars[c] = c;
759  }
760  __Pyx_sys_getdefaultencoding_not_ascii = 1;
761  ascii_chars_u = PyUnicode_DecodeASCII(ascii_chars, 128, NULL);
762  if (!ascii_chars_u) goto bad;
763  ascii_chars_b = PyUnicode_AsEncodedString(ascii_chars_u, default_encoding_c, NULL);
764  if (!ascii_chars_b || !PyBytes_Check(ascii_chars_b) || memcmp(ascii_chars, PyBytes_AS_STRING(ascii_chars_b), 128) != 0) {
765  PyErr_Format(
766  PyExc_ValueError,
767  "This module compiled with c_string_encoding=ascii, but default encoding '%.200s' is not a superset of ascii.",
768  default_encoding_c);
769  goto bad;
770  }
771  Py_DECREF(ascii_chars_u);
772  Py_DECREF(ascii_chars_b);
773  }
774  Py_DECREF(default_encoding);
775  return 0;
776 bad:
777  Py_XDECREF(default_encoding);
778  Py_XDECREF(ascii_chars_u);
779  Py_XDECREF(ascii_chars_b);
780  return -1;
781 }
782 #endif

11591  if (num_found < num_min) {
11592  num_expected = num_min;
11593  more_or_less = "at least";
11594  } else {
11595  num_expected = num_max;
11596  more_or_less = "at most";
11597  }
11598  if (exact) {
11599  more_or_less = "exactly";
11600  }
11601  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
11602  "%.200s() takes %.8s %" CYTHON_FORMAT_SSIZE_T "d positional argument%.1s (%" CYTHON_FORMAT_SSIZE_T "d given)",
11603  func_name, more_or_less, num_expected,
11604  (num_expected == 1) ? "" : "s", num_found);
11605 }
11606 
11607 /* RaiseDoubleKeywords */
11608 static void __Pyx_RaiseDoubleKeywordsError(
11609  const char* func_name,
11610  PyObject* kw_name)
11611 {
11612  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
11613  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
11614  "%s() got multiple values for keyword argument '%U'", func_name, kw_name);
11615  #else
11616  "%s() got multiple values for keyword argument '%s'", func_name,
11617  PyString_AsString(kw_name));
11618  #endif
11619 }

11621 /* ParseKeywords */
11622 static int __Pyx_ParseOptionalKeywords(
11623  PyObject *kwds,
11624  PyObject **argnames[],
11625  PyObject *kwds2,
11626  PyObject *values[],
11627  Py_ssize_t num_pos_args,
11628  const char* function_name)
11629 {
11630  PyObject *key = 0, *value = 0;
11631  Py_ssize_t pos = 0;
11632  PyObject*** name;
11633  PyObject*** first_kw_arg = argnames + num_pos_args;
11634  while (PyDict_Next(kwds, &pos, &key, &value)) {
11635  name = first_kw_arg;
11636  while (*name && (**name != key)) name++;
11637  if (*name) {
11638  values[name-argnames] = value;
11639  continue;
11640  }
11641  name = first_kw_arg;
11642  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
11643  if (likely(PyString_CheckExact(key)) || likely(PyString_Check(key))) {
11644  while (*name) {
11645  if ((CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY || PyString_GET_SIZE(**name) == PyString_GET_SIZE(key))
11646  && _PyString_Eq(**name, key)) {
11647  values[name-argnames] = value;
11648  break;
11649  }
11650  name++;
11651  }
11652  if (*name) continue;
11653  else {
11654  PyObject*** argname = argnames;
11655  while (argname != first_kw_arg) {
11656  if ((**argname == key) || (
11657  (CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY || PyString_GET_SIZE(**argname) == PyString_GET_SIZE(key))
11658  && _PyString_Eq(**argname, key))) {
11659  goto arg_passed_twice;
11660  }
11661  argname++;
11662  }
11663  }
11664  } else
11665  #endif
11666  if (likely(PyUnicode_Check(key))) {
11667  while (*name) {
11668  int cmp = (**name == key) ? 0 :
11669  #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY && PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
11670  (PyUnicode_GET_SIZE(**name) != PyUnicode_GET_SIZE(key)) ? 1 :
11671  #endif
11672  PyUnicode_Compare(**name, key);
11673  if (cmp < 0 && unlikely(PyErr_Occurred())) goto bad;
11674  if (cmp == 0) {
11675  values[name-argnames] = value;
11676  break;
11677  }
11678  name++;
11679  }
11680  if (*name) continue;
11681  else {
11682  PyObject*** argname = argnames;
11683  while (argname != first_kw_arg) {
11684  int cmp = (**argname == key) ? 0 :
11685  #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY && PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
11686  (PyUnicode_GET_SIZE(**argname) != PyUnicode_GET_SIZE(key)) ? 1 :
11687  #endif
11688  PyUnicode_Compare(**argname, key);
11689  if (cmp < 0 && unlikely(PyErr_Occurred())) goto bad;
11690  if (cmp == 0) goto arg_passed_twice;
11691  argname++;
11692  }
11693  }
11694  } else
11695  goto invalid_keyword_type;
11696  if (kwds2) {
11697  if (unlikely(PyDict_SetItem(kwds2, key, value))) goto bad;
11698  } else {
11699  goto invalid_keyword;
11700  }
11701  }
11702  return 0;
11703 arg_passed_twice:
11704  __Pyx_RaiseDoubleKeywordsError(function_name, key);
11705  goto bad;
11706 invalid_keyword_type:
11707  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
11708  "%.200s() keywords must be strings", function_name);
11709  goto bad;
11710 invalid_keyword:
11711  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
11712  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
11713  "%.200s() got an unexpected keyword argument '%.200s'",
11714  function_name, PyString_AsString(key));
11715  #else
11716  "%s() got an unexpected keyword argument '%U'",
11717  function_name, key);
11718  #endif
11719 bad:
11720  return -1;
11721 }

11723 /* ArgTypeTest */
11724 static int __Pyx__ArgTypeTest(PyObject *obj, PyTypeObject *type, const char *name, int exact)
11725 {
11726  if (unlikely(!type)) {
11727  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_SystemError, "Missing type object");
11728  return 0;
11729  }
11730  else if (exact) {
11731  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION == 2
11732  if ((type == &PyBaseString_Type) && likely(__Pyx_PyBaseString_CheckExact(obj))) return 1;
11733  #endif
11734  }
11735  else {
11736  if (likely(__Pyx_TypeCheck(obj, type))) return 1;
11737  }
11738  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
11739  "Argument '%.200s' has incorrect type (expected %.200s, got %.200s)",
11740  name, type->tp_name, Py_TYPE(obj)->tp_name);
11741  return 0;
11742 }

11744 /* PyFunctionFastCall */
11745 #if CYTHON_FAST_PYCALL
11746 static PyObject* __Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallNoKw(PyCodeObject *co, PyObject **args, Py_ssize_t na,
11747  PyObject *globals) {
11748  PyFrameObject *f;
11749  PyThreadState *tstate = __Pyx_PyThreadState_Current;
11750  PyObject **fastlocals;
11751  Py_ssize_t i;
11752  PyObject *result;
11753  assert(globals != NULL);
11754  /* XXX Perhaps we should create a specialized
11755  PyFrame_New() that doesn't take locals, but does
11756  take builtins without sanity checking them.
11757  */
11758  assert(tstate != NULL);
11759  f = PyFrame_New(tstate, co, globals, NULL);
11760  if (f == NULL) {
11761  return NULL;
11762  }
11763  fastlocals = __Pyx_PyFrame_GetLocalsplus(f);
11764  for (i = 0; i < na; i++) {
11765  Py_INCREF(*args);
11766  fastlocals[i] = *args++;
11767  }
11768  result = PyEval_EvalFrameEx(f,0);
11769  ++tstate->recursion_depth;
11770  Py_DECREF(f);
11771  --tstate->recursion_depth;
11772  return result;
11773 }
11774 #if 1 || PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030600B1
11775 static PyObject *__Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallDict(PyObject *func, PyObject **args, int nargs, PyObject *kwargs) {
11776  PyCodeObject *co = (PyCodeObject *)PyFunction_GET_CODE(func);
11777  PyObject *globals = PyFunction_GET_GLOBALS(func);
11778  PyObject *argdefs = PyFunction_GET_DEFAULTS(func);
11779  PyObject *closure;
11780 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
11781  PyObject *kwdefs;
11782 #endif
11783  PyObject *kwtuple, **k;
11784  PyObject **d;
11785  Py_ssize_t nd;
11786  Py_ssize_t nk;
11787  PyObject *result;
11788  assert(kwargs == NULL || PyDict_Check(kwargs));
11789  nk = kwargs ? PyDict_Size(kwargs) : 0;
11790  if (Py_EnterRecursiveCall((char*)" while calling a Python object")) {
11791  return NULL;
11792  }
11793  if (
11794 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
11795  co->co_kwonlyargcount == 0 &&
11796 #endif
11797  likely(kwargs == NULL || nk == 0) &&
11798  co->co_flags == (CO_OPTIMIZED | CO_NEWLOCALS | CO_NOFREE)) {
11799  if (argdefs == NULL && co->co_argcount == nargs) {
11800  result = __Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallNoKw(co, args, nargs, globals);
11801  goto done;
11802  }
11803  else if (nargs == 0 && argdefs != NULL
11804  && co->co_argcount == Py_SIZE(argdefs)) {
11805  /* function called with no arguments, but all parameters have
11806  a default value: use default values as arguments .*/
11807  args = &PyTuple_GET_ITEM(argdefs, 0);
11808  result =__Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallNoKw(co, args, Py_SIZE(argdefs), globals);
11809  goto done;
11810  }
11811  }
11812  if (kwargs != NULL) {
11813  Py_ssize_t pos, i;
11814  kwtuple = PyTuple_New(2 * nk);
11815  if (kwtuple == NULL) {
11816  result = NULL;
11817  goto done;
11818  }
11819  k = &PyTuple_GET_ITEM(kwtuple, 0);
11820  pos = i = 0;
11821  while (PyDict_Next(kwargs, &pos, &k[i], &k[i+1])) {
11822  Py_INCREF(k[i]);
11823  Py_INCREF(k[i+1]);
11824  i += 2;
11825  }
11826  nk = i / 2;
11827  }
11828  else {
11829  kwtuple = NULL;
11830  k = NULL;
11831  }
11832  closure = PyFunction_GET_CLOSURE(func);
11833 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
11834  kwdefs = PyFunction_GET_KW_DEFAULTS(func);
11835 #endif
11836  if (argdefs != NULL) {
11837  d = &PyTuple_GET_ITEM(argdefs, 0);
11838  nd = Py_SIZE(argdefs);
11839  }
11840  else {
11841  d = NULL;
11842  nd = 0;
11843  }
11844 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
11845  result = PyEval_EvalCodeEx((PyObject*)co, globals, (PyObject *)NULL,
11846  args, nargs,
11847  k, (int)nk,
11848  d, (int)nd, kwdefs, closure);
11849 #else
11850  result = PyEval_EvalCodeEx(co, globals, (PyObject *)NULL,
11851  args, nargs,
11852  k, (int)nk,
11853  d, (int)nd, closure);
11854 #endif
11855  Py_XDECREF(kwtuple);
11856 done:
11857  Py_LeaveRecursiveCall();
11858  return result;
11859 }
11860 #endif
11861 #endif
11862 
11863 /* PyObjectCall */
11864 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
11865 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_Call(PyObject *func, PyObject *arg, PyObject *kw) {
11866  PyObject *result;
11867  ternaryfunc call = func->ob_type->tp_call;
11868  if (unlikely(!call))
11869  return PyObject_Call(func, arg, kw);
11870  if (unlikely(Py_EnterRecursiveCall((char*)" while calling a Python object")))
11871  return NULL;
11872  result = (*call)(func, arg, kw);
11873  Py_LeaveRecursiveCall();
11874  if (unlikely(!result) && unlikely(!PyErr_Occurred())) {
11875  PyErr_SetString(
11876  PyExc_SystemError,
11877  "NULL result without error in PyObject_Call");
11878  }
11879  return result;
11880 }
11881 #endif

11883 /* PyObjectCallMethO */
11884 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
11885 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_CallMethO(PyObject *func, PyObject *arg) {
11886  PyObject *self, *result;

11888  cfunc = PyCFunction_GET_FUNCTION(func);

11890  if (unlikely(Py_EnterRecursiveCall((char*)" while calling a Python object")))
11891  return NULL;
11892  result = cfunc(self, arg);
11893  Py_LeaveRecursiveCall();
11894  if (unlikely(!result) && unlikely(!PyErr_Occurred())) {
11895  PyErr_SetString(
11896  PyExc_SystemError,
11897  "NULL result without error in PyObject_Call");
11898  }
11899  return result;
11900 }

11925 /* PyCFunctionFastCall */
11926 #if CYTHON_FAST_PYCCALL
11927 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject * __Pyx_PyCFunction_FastCall(PyObject *func_obj, PyObject **args, Py_ssize_t nargs) {
11928  PyCFunctionObject *func = (PyCFunctionObject*)func_obj;

11934  assert(nargs >= 0);

11937  because it may clear it (directly or indirectly) and so the

11941  return (*((__Pyx_PyCFunctionFastWithKeywords)(void*)meth)) (self, args, nargs, NULL);

12001 /* IterFinish */
12002 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_IterFinish(void) {
12003 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
12004  PyThreadState *tstate = __Pyx_PyThreadState_Current;
12005  PyObject* exc_type = tstate->curexc_type;
12006  if (unlikely(exc_type)) {
12007  if (likely(__Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(exc_type, PyExc_StopIteration))) {
12008  PyObject *exc_value, *exc_tb;
12009  exc_value = tstate->curexc_value;
12010  exc_tb = tstate->curexc_traceback;
12011  tstate->curexc_type = 0;
12012  tstate->curexc_value = 0;
12013  tstate->curexc_traceback = 0;
12014  Py_DECREF(exc_type);
12015  Py_XDECREF(exc_value);
12016  Py_XDECREF(exc_tb);
12017  return 0;
12018  } else {
12019  return -1;
12020  }
12021  }
12022  return 0;
12023 #else
12024  if (unlikely(PyErr_Occurred())) {
12025  if (likely(PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_StopIteration))) {
12026  PyErr_Clear();
12027  return 0;
12028  } else {
12029  return -1;
12030  }
12031  }
12032  return 0;
12033 #endif
12034 }

12085 /* RaiseException */
12086 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
12087 static void __Pyx_Raise(PyObject *type, PyObject *value, PyObject *tb,
12088  CYTHON_UNUSED PyObject *cause) {
12089  __Pyx_PyThreadState_declare
12090  Py_XINCREF(type);
12091  if (!value || value == Py_None)
12092  value = NULL;
12093  else
12094  Py_INCREF(value);
12095  if (!tb || tb == Py_None)
12096  tb = NULL;
12097  else {
12098  Py_INCREF(tb);
12099  if (!PyTraceBack_Check(tb)) {
12100  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
12101  "raise: arg 3 must be a traceback or None");
12102  goto raise_error;
12103  }
12104  }
12105  if (PyType_Check(type)) {
12106 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
12107  if (!value) {
12108  Py_INCREF(Py_None);
12109  value = Py_None;
12110  }
12111 #endif
12112  PyErr_NormalizeException(&type, &value, &tb);
12113  } else {
12114  if (value) {
12115  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
12116  "instance exception may not have a separate value");
12117  goto raise_error;
12118  }
12119  value = type;
12120  type = (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(type);
12121  Py_INCREF(type);
12122  if (!PyType_IsSubtype((PyTypeObject *)type, (PyTypeObject *)PyExc_BaseException)) {
12123  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
12124  "raise: exception class must be a subclass of BaseException");
12125  goto raise_error;
12126  }
12127  }
12128  __Pyx_PyThreadState_assign
12129  __Pyx_ErrRestore(type, value, tb);
12130  return;
12131 raise_error:
12132  Py_XDECREF(value);
12133  Py_XDECREF(type);
12134  Py_XDECREF(tb);
12135  return;
12136 }
12137 #else
12138 static void __Pyx_Raise(PyObject *type, PyObject *value, PyObject *tb, PyObject *cause) {
12139  PyObject* owned_instance = NULL;
12140  if (tb == Py_None) {
12141  tb = 0;
12142  } else if (tb && !PyTraceBack_Check(tb)) {
12143  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
12144  "raise: arg 3 must be a traceback or None");
12145  goto bad;
12146  }
12147  if (value == Py_None)
12148  value = 0;
12149  if (PyExceptionInstance_Check(type)) {
12150  if (value) {
12151  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
12152  "instance exception may not have a separate value");
12153  goto bad;
12154  }
12155  value = type;
12156  type = (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(value);
12157  } else if (PyExceptionClass_Check(type)) {
12158  PyObject *instance_class = NULL;
12159  if (value && PyExceptionInstance_Check(value)) {
12160  instance_class = (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(value);
12161  if (instance_class != type) {
12162  int is_subclass = PyObject_IsSubclass(instance_class, type);
12163  if (!is_subclass) {
12164  instance_class = NULL;
12165  } else if (unlikely(is_subclass == -1)) {
12166  goto bad;
12167  } else {
12168  type = instance_class;
12169  }
12170  }
12171  }
12172  if (!instance_class) {
12173  PyObject *args;
12174  if (!value)
12175  args = PyTuple_New(0);
12176  else if (PyTuple_Check(value)) {
12177  Py_INCREF(value);
12178  args = value;
12179  } else
12180  args = PyTuple_Pack(1, value);
12181  if (!args)
12182  goto bad;
12183  owned_instance = PyObject_Call(type, args, NULL);
12184  Py_DECREF(args);
12185  if (!owned_instance)
12186  goto bad;
12187  value = owned_instance;
12188  if (!PyExceptionInstance_Check(value)) {
12189  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
12190  "calling %R should have returned an instance of "
12191  "BaseException, not %R",
12192  type, Py_TYPE(value));
12193  goto bad;
12194  }
12195  }
12196  } else {
12197  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
12198  "raise: exception class must be a subclass of BaseException");
12199  goto bad;
12200  }
12201  if (cause) {
12202  PyObject *fixed_cause;
12203  if (cause == Py_None) {
12204  fixed_cause = NULL;
12205  } else if (PyExceptionClass_Check(cause)) {
12206  fixed_cause = PyObject_CallObject(cause, NULL);
12207  if (fixed_cause == NULL)
12208  goto bad;
12209  } else if (PyExceptionInstance_Check(cause)) {
12210  fixed_cause = cause;
12211  Py_INCREF(fixed_cause);
12212  } else {
12213  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
12214  "exception causes must derive from "
12215  "BaseException");
12216  goto bad;
12217  }
12218  PyException_SetCause(value, fixed_cause);
12219  }
12220  PyErr_SetObject(type, value);
12221  if (tb) {
12222 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
12223  PyObject *tmp_type, *tmp_value, *tmp_tb;
12224  PyErr_Fetch(&tmp_type, &tmp_value, &tmp_tb);
12225  Py_INCREF(tb);
12226  PyErr_Restore(tmp_type, tmp_value, tb);
12227  Py_XDECREF(tmp_tb);
12228 #else
12229  PyThreadState *tstate = __Pyx_PyThreadState_Current;
12230  PyObject* tmp_tb = tstate->curexc_traceback;
12231  if (tb != tmp_tb) {
12232  Py_INCREF(tb);
12233  tstate->curexc_traceback = tb;
12234  Py_XDECREF(tmp_tb);
12235  }
12236 #endif
12237  }
12238 bad:
12239  Py_XDECREF(owned_instance);
12240  return;
12241 }
12242 #endif
12243 
12244 /* DictGetItem */
12245 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3 && !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
12246 static PyObject *__Pyx_PyDict_GetItem(PyObject *d, PyObject* key) {
12247  PyObject *value;
12248  value = PyDict_GetItemWithError(d, key);
12249  if (unlikely(!value)) {
12250  if (!PyErr_Occurred()) {
12251  if (unlikely(PyTuple_Check(key))) {
12252  PyObject* args = PyTuple_Pack(1, key);
12253  if (likely(args)) {
12254  PyErr_SetObject(PyExc_KeyError, args);
12255  Py_DECREF(args);
12256  }
12257  } else {
12258  PyErr_SetObject(PyExc_KeyError, key);
12259  }
12260  }
12261  return NULL;
12262  }
12263  Py_INCREF(value);
12264  return value;
12265 }

12329 /* PyErrExceptionMatches */
12330 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
12331 static int __Pyx_PyErr_ExceptionMatchesTuple(PyObject *exc_type, PyObject *tuple) {
12332  Py_ssize_t i, n;
12333  n = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(tuple);
12334 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
12335  for (i=0; i<n; i++) {
12336  if (exc_type == PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tuple, i)) return 1;
12337  }
12338 #endif
12339  for (i=0; i<n; i++) {
12340  if (__Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(exc_type, PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tuple, i))) return 1;
12341  }
12342  return 0;
12343 }
12344 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyErr_ExceptionMatchesInState(PyThreadState* tstate, PyObject* err) {
12345  PyObject *exc_type = tstate->curexc_type;
12346  if (exc_type == err) return 1;
12347  if (unlikely(!exc_type)) return 0;
12348  if (unlikely(PyTuple_Check(err)))
12349  return __Pyx_PyErr_ExceptionMatchesTuple(exc_type, err);
12350  return __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(exc_type, err);
12351 }
12352 #endif

12354 /* GetException */
12355 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
12356 static int __Pyx__GetException(PyThreadState *tstate, PyObject **type, PyObject **value, PyObject **tb)
12357 #else
12358 static int __Pyx_GetException(PyObject **type, PyObject **value, PyObject **tb)

12360 {

12368  tstate->curexc_value = 0;

12370 #else

12374 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE

12378 #endif
12379  goto bad;
12380  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3

12382  if (unlikely(PyException_SetTraceback(local_value, local_tb) < 0))
12383  goto bad;
12384  }
12385  #endif
12386  Py_XINCREF(local_tb);
12387  Py_XINCREF(local_type);
12388  Py_XINCREF(local_value);

12390  *value = local_value;
12391  *tb = local_tb;
12392 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE

12403  #else

12408  tstate->exc_value = local_value;
12409  tstate->exc_traceback = local_tb;
12410  #endif

12412  Py_XDECREF(tmp_value);
12413  Py_XDECREF(tmp_tb);
12414 #else
12415  PyErr_SetExcInfo(local_type, local_value, local_tb);
12416 #endif

12420  *value = 0;
12421  *tb = 0;

12429 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS && CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP && PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x03070000
12430 static PyObject *__Pyx_RaiseGenericGetAttributeError(PyTypeObject *tp, PyObject *attr_name) {
12431  PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,

12441 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_GenericGetAttrNoDict(PyObject* obj, PyObject* attr_name) {
12442  PyObject *descr;
12443  PyTypeObject *tp = Py_TYPE(obj);
12444  if (unlikely(!PyString_Check(attr_name))) {
12445  return PyObject_GenericGetAttr(obj, attr_name);
12446  }
12447  assert(!tp->tp_dictoffset);
12448  descr = _PyType_Lookup(tp, attr_name);
12449  if (unlikely(!descr)) {
12450  return __Pyx_RaiseGenericGetAttributeError(tp, attr_name);
12451  }
12452  Py_INCREF(descr);
12453  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
12454  if (likely(PyType_HasFeature(Py_TYPE(descr), Py_TPFLAGS_HAVE_CLASS)))
12455  #endif
12456  {
12457  descrgetfunc f = Py_TYPE(descr)->tp_descr_get;
12458  if (unlikely(f)) {
12459  PyObject *res = f(descr, obj, (PyObject *)tp);
12460  Py_DECREF(descr);
12461  return res;
12462  }
12463  }
12464  return descr;
12465 }
12466 #endif

12478 /* SetupReduce */
12479 static int __Pyx_setup_reduce_is_named(PyObject* meth, PyObject* name) {
12480  int ret;
12481  PyObject *name_attr;
12482  name_attr = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(meth, __pyx_n_s_name);
12483  if (likely(name_attr)) {
12484  ret = PyObject_RichCompareBool(name_attr, name, Py_EQ);
12485  } else {
12486  ret = -1;
12487  }
12488  if (unlikely(ret < 0)) {
12489  PyErr_Clear();
12490  ret = 0;
12491  }
12492  Py_XDECREF(name_attr);
12493  return ret;
12494 }
12495 static int __Pyx_setup_reduce(PyObject* type_obj) {
12496  int ret = 0;
12497  PyObject *object_reduce = NULL;
12498  PyObject *object_reduce_ex = NULL;
12499  PyObject *reduce = NULL;
12500  PyObject *reduce_ex = NULL;
12501  PyObject *reduce_cython = NULL;
12502  PyObject *setstate = NULL;
12503  PyObject *setstate_cython = NULL;
12504 #if CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP
12505  if (_PyType_Lookup((PyTypeObject*)type_obj, __pyx_n_s_getstate)) goto GOOD;
12506 #else
12507  if (PyObject_HasAttr(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_getstate)) goto GOOD;
12508 #endif
12509 #if CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP
12510  object_reduce_ex = _PyType_Lookup(&PyBaseObject_Type, __pyx_n_s_reduce_ex); if (!object_reduce_ex) goto BAD;
12511 #else
12512  object_reduce_ex = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr((PyObject*)&PyBaseObject_Type, __pyx_n_s_reduce_ex); if (!object_reduce_ex) goto BAD;
12513 #endif
12514  reduce_ex = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_reduce_ex); if (unlikely(!reduce_ex)) goto BAD;
12515  if (reduce_ex == object_reduce_ex) {
12516 #if CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP
12517  object_reduce = _PyType_Lookup(&PyBaseObject_Type, __pyx_n_s_reduce); if (!object_reduce) goto BAD;
12518 #else
12519  object_reduce = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr((PyObject*)&PyBaseObject_Type, __pyx_n_s_reduce); if (!object_reduce) goto BAD;
12520 #endif
12521  reduce = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_reduce); if (unlikely(!reduce)) goto BAD;
12522  if (reduce == object_reduce || __Pyx_setup_reduce_is_named(reduce, __pyx_n_s_reduce_cython)) {
12523  reduce_cython = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_reduce_cython); if (unlikely(!reduce_cython)) goto BAD;
12524  ret = PyDict_SetItem(((PyTypeObject*)type_obj)->tp_dict, __pyx_n_s_reduce, reduce_cython); if (unlikely(ret < 0)) goto BAD;
12525  ret = PyDict_DelItem(((PyTypeObject*)type_obj)->tp_dict, __pyx_n_s_reduce_cython); if (unlikely(ret < 0)) goto BAD;
12526  setstate = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_setstate);
12527  if (!setstate) PyErr_Clear();
12528  if (!setstate || __Pyx_setup_reduce_is_named(setstate, __pyx_n_s_setstate_cython)) {
12529  setstate_cython = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_setstate_cython); if (unlikely(!setstate_cython)) goto BAD;
12530  ret = PyDict_SetItem(((PyTypeObject*)type_obj)->tp_dict, __pyx_n_s_setstate, setstate_cython); if (unlikely(ret < 0)) goto BAD;
12531  ret = PyDict_DelItem(((PyTypeObject*)type_obj)->tp_dict, __pyx_n_s_setstate_cython); if (unlikely(ret < 0)) goto BAD;
12532  }
12533  PyType_Modified((PyTypeObject*)type_obj);
12534  }
12535  }
12536  goto GOOD;
12537 BAD:
12538  if (!PyErr_Occurred())
12539  PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError, "Unable to initialize pickling for %s", ((PyTypeObject*)type_obj)->tp_name);
12540  ret = -1;
12541 GOOD:
12542 #if !CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP
12543  Py_XDECREF(object_reduce);
12544  Py_XDECREF(object_reduce_ex);
12545 #endif
12546  Py_XDECREF(reduce);
12547  Py_XDECREF(reduce_ex);
12548  Py_XDECREF(reduce_cython);
12549  Py_XDECREF(setstate);
12550  Py_XDECREF(setstate_cython);
12551  return ret;
12552 }

12554 /* TypeImport */
12555 #ifndef __PYX_HAVE_RT_ImportType
12556 #define __PYX_HAVE_RT_ImportType
12557 static PyTypeObject *__Pyx_ImportType(PyObject *module, const char *module_name, const char *class_name,
12558  size_t size, enum __Pyx_ImportType_CheckSize check_size)
12559 {
12560  PyObject *result = 0;
12561  char warning[200];
12562  Py_ssize_t basicsize;
12563 #ifdef Py_LIMITED_API
12564  PyObject *py_basicsize;
12565 #endif
12566  result = PyObject_GetAttrString(module, class_name);
12567  if (!result)
12568  goto bad;
12569  if (!PyType_Check(result)) {
12570  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
12571  "%.200s.%.200s is not a type object",
12572  module_name, class_name);
12573  goto bad;
12574  }
12575 #ifndef Py_LIMITED_API
12576  basicsize = ((PyTypeObject *)result)->tp_basicsize;
12577 #else
12578  py_basicsize = PyObject_GetAttrString(result, "__basicsize__");
12579  if (!py_basicsize)
12580  goto bad;
12581  basicsize = PyLong_AsSsize_t(py_basicsize);
12582  Py_DECREF(py_basicsize);
12583  py_basicsize = 0;
12584  if (basicsize == (Py_ssize_t)-1 && PyErr_Occurred())
12585  goto bad;
12586 #endif
12587  if ((size_t)basicsize < size) {
12588  PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
12589  "%.200s.%.200s size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility. "
12590  "Expected %zd from C header, got %zd from PyObject",
12591  module_name, class_name, size, basicsize);
12592  goto bad;
12593  }
12594  if (check_size == __Pyx_ImportType_CheckSize_Error && (size_t)basicsize != size) {
12595  PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
12596  "%.200s.%.200s size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility. "
12597  "Expected %zd from C header, got %zd from PyObject",
12598  module_name, class_name, size, basicsize);
12599  goto bad;
12600  }
12601  else if (check_size == __Pyx_ImportType_CheckSize_Warn && (size_t)basicsize > size) {
12602  PyOS_snprintf(warning, sizeof(warning),
12603  "%s.%s size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility. "
12604  "Expected %zd from C header, got %zd from PyObject",
12605  module_name, class_name, size, basicsize);
12606  if (PyErr_WarnEx(NULL, warning, 0) < 0) goto bad;
12607  }
12608  return (PyTypeObject *)result;
12609 bad:
12610  Py_XDECREF(result);
12611  return NULL;
12612 }
12613 #endif

12615 /* Import */
12616 static PyObject *__Pyx_Import(PyObject *name, PyObject *from_list, int level) {
12617  PyObject *empty_list = 0;
12618  PyObject *module = 0;
12619  PyObject *global_dict = 0;
12620  PyObject *empty_dict = 0;
12621  PyObject *list;
12622  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
12623  PyObject *py_import;
12624  py_import = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(__pyx_b, __pyx_n_s_import);
12625  if (!py_import)
12626  goto bad;
12627  #endif
12628  if (from_list)
12629  list = from_list;
12630  else {
12631  empty_list = PyList_New(0);
12632  if (!empty_list)
12633  goto bad;
12634  list = empty_list;
12635  }
12636  global_dict = PyModule_GetDict(__pyx_m);
12637  if (!global_dict)
12638  goto bad;
12639  empty_dict = PyDict_New();
12640  if (!empty_dict)
12641  goto bad;
12642  {
12643  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
12644  if (level == -1) {
12645  if (strchr(__Pyx_MODULE_NAME, '.')) {
12646  module = PyImport_ImportModuleLevelObject(
12647  name, global_dict, empty_dict, list, 1);
12648  if (!module) {
12649  if (!PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_ImportError))
12650  goto bad;
12651  PyErr_Clear();
12652  }
12653  }
12654  level = 0;
12655  }
12656  #endif
12657  if (!module) {
12658  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
12659  PyObject *py_level = PyInt_FromLong(level);
12660  if (!py_level)
12661  goto bad;
12662  module = PyObject_CallFunctionObjArgs(py_import,
12663  name, global_dict, empty_dict, list, py_level, (PyObject *)NULL);
12664  Py_DECREF(py_level);
12665  #else
12666  module = PyImport_ImportModuleLevelObject(
12667  name, global_dict, empty_dict, list, level);
12668  #endif
12669  }
12670  }
12671 bad:
12672  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
12673  Py_XDECREF(py_import);
12674  #endif
12675  Py_XDECREF(empty_list);
12676  Py_XDECREF(empty_dict);
12677  return module;
12678 }

12684  PyErr_Format(PyExc_ImportError,
12685  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
12686  "cannot import name %.230s", PyString_AS_STRING(name));
12687  #else

12689  #endif
12690  }

12694 /* CLineInTraceback */
12695 #ifndef CYTHON_CLINE_IN_TRACEBACK
12696 static int __Pyx_CLineForTraceback(PyThreadState *tstate, int c_line) {
12697  PyObject *use_cline;
12698  PyObject *ptype, *pvalue, *ptraceback;
12699 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
12700  PyObject **cython_runtime_dict;
12701 #endif
12702  if (unlikely(!__pyx_cython_runtime)) {
12703  return c_line;
12704  }
12705  __Pyx_ErrFetchInState(tstate, &ptype, &pvalue, &ptraceback);
12706 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
12707  cython_runtime_dict = _PyObject_GetDictPtr(__pyx_cython_runtime);
12708  if (likely(cython_runtime_dict)) {
12709  __PYX_PY_DICT_LOOKUP_IF_MODIFIED(
12710  use_cline, *cython_runtime_dict,
12711  __Pyx_PyDict_GetItemStr(*cython_runtime_dict, __pyx_n_s_cline_in_traceback))
12712  } else
12713 #endif
12714  {
12715  PyObject *use_cline_obj = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(__pyx_cython_runtime, __pyx_n_s_cline_in_traceback);
12716  if (use_cline_obj) {
12717  use_cline = PyObject_Not(use_cline_obj) ? Py_False : Py_True;
12718  Py_DECREF(use_cline_obj);
12719  } else {
12720  PyErr_Clear();
12721  use_cline = NULL;
12722  }
12723  }
12724  if (!use_cline) {
12725  c_line = 0;
12726  PyObject_SetAttr(__pyx_cython_runtime, __pyx_n_s_cline_in_traceback, Py_False);
12727  }
12728  else if (use_cline == Py_False || (use_cline != Py_True && PyObject_Not(use_cline) != 0)) {
12729  c_line = 0;
12730  }
12731  __Pyx_ErrRestoreInState(tstate, ptype, pvalue, ptraceback);
12732  return c_line;
12733 }

12736 /* CodeObjectCache */
12737 static int __pyx_bisect_code_objects(__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry* entries, int count, int code_line) {
12738  int start = 0, mid = 0, end = count - 1;
12739  if (end >= 0 && code_line > entries[end].code_line) {
12740  return count;
12741  }
12742  while (start < end) {
12743  mid = start + (end - start) / 2;
12744  if (code_line < entries[mid].code_line) {
12745  end = mid;
12746  } else if (code_line > entries[mid].code_line) {
12747  start = mid + 1;
12748  } else {
12749  return mid;
12750  }
12751  }
12752  if (code_line <= entries[mid].code_line) {
12753  return mid;
12754  } else {
12755  return mid + 1;
12756  }
12757 }
12758 static PyCodeObject *__pyx_find_code_object(int code_line) {
12759  PyCodeObject* code_object;
12760  int pos;
12761  if (unlikely(!code_line) || unlikely(!__pyx_code_cache.entries)) {
12762  return NULL;
12763  }
12764  pos = __pyx_bisect_code_objects(__pyx_code_cache.entries, __pyx_code_cache.count, code_line);
12765  if (unlikely(pos >= __pyx_code_cache.count) || unlikely(__pyx_code_cache.entries[pos].code_line != code_line)) {
12766  return NULL;
12767  }
12768  code_object = __pyx_code_cache.entries[pos].code_object;
12769  Py_INCREF(code_object);
12770  return code_object;
12771 }
12772 static void __pyx_insert_code_object(int code_line, PyCodeObject* code_object) {
12773  int pos, i;
12774  __Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry* entries = __pyx_code_cache.entries;
12775  if (unlikely(!code_line)) {
12776  return;
12777  }
12778  if (unlikely(!entries)) {
12779  entries = (__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry*)PyMem_Malloc(64*sizeof(__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry));
12780  if (likely(entries)) {
12781  __pyx_code_cache.entries = entries;
12782  __pyx_code_cache.max_count = 64;
12783  __pyx_code_cache.count = 1;
12784  entries[0].code_line = code_line;
12785  entries[0].code_object = code_object;
12786  Py_INCREF(code_object);
12787  }
12788  return;
12789  }
12790  pos = __pyx_bisect_code_objects(__pyx_code_cache.entries, __pyx_code_cache.count, code_line);
12791  if ((pos < __pyx_code_cache.count) && unlikely(__pyx_code_cache.entries[pos].code_line == code_line)) {
12792  PyCodeObject* tmp = entries[pos].code_object;
12793  entries[pos].code_object = code_object;
12794  Py_DECREF(tmp);
12795  return;
12796  }
12797  if (__pyx_code_cache.count == __pyx_code_cache.max_count) {
12798  int new_max = __pyx_code_cache.max_count + 64;
12799  entries = (__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry*)PyMem_Realloc(
12800  __pyx_code_cache.entries, (size_t)new_max*sizeof(__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry));
12801  if (unlikely(!entries)) {
12802  return;
12803  }
12804  __pyx_code_cache.entries = entries;
12805  __pyx_code_cache.max_count = new_max;
12806  }
12807  for (i=__pyx_code_cache.count; i>pos; i--) {
12808  entries[i] = entries[i-1];
12809  }
12810  entries[pos].code_line = code_line;
12811  entries[pos].code_object = code_object;
12812  __pyx_code_cache.count++;
12813  Py_INCREF(code_object);
12814 }

12816 /* AddTraceback */
12817 #include "compile.h"
12818 #include "frameobject.h"
12819 #include "traceback.h"
12820 static PyCodeObject* __Pyx_CreateCodeObjectForTraceback(
12821  const char *funcname, int c_line,
12822  int py_line, const char *filename) {
12823  PyCodeObject *py_code = 0;
12824  PyObject *py_srcfile = 0;
12825  PyObject *py_funcname = 0;
12826  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
12827  py_srcfile = PyString_FromString(filename);
12828  #else
12829  py_srcfile = PyUnicode_FromString(filename);
12830  #endif
12831  if (!py_srcfile) goto bad;
12832  if (c_line) {
12833  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
12834  py_funcname = PyString_FromFormat( "%s (%s:%d)", funcname, __pyx_cfilenm, c_line);
12835  #else
12836  py_funcname = PyUnicode_FromFormat( "%s (%s:%d)", funcname, __pyx_cfilenm, c_line);
12837  #endif
12838  }
12839  else {
12840  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
12841  py_funcname = PyString_FromString(funcname);
12842  #else
12843  py_funcname = PyUnicode_FromString(funcname);
12844  #endif
12845  }
12846  if (!py_funcname) goto bad;
12847  py_code = __Pyx_PyCode_New(
12848  0,
12849  0,
12850  0,
12851  0,
12852  0,
12853  __pyx_empty_bytes, /*PyObject *code,*/
12854  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *consts,*/
12855  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *names,*/
12856  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *varnames,*/
12857  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *freevars,*/
12858  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *cellvars,*/
12859  py_srcfile, /*PyObject *filename,*/
12860  py_funcname, /*PyObject *name,*/
12861  py_line,
12862  __pyx_empty_bytes /*PyObject *lnotab*/
12863  );
12864  Py_DECREF(py_srcfile);
12865  Py_DECREF(py_funcname);
12866  return py_code;
12867 bad:
12868  Py_XDECREF(py_srcfile);
12869  Py_XDECREF(py_funcname);
12870  return NULL;
12871 }
12872 static void __Pyx_AddTraceback(const char *funcname, int c_line,
12873  int py_line, const char *filename) {
12874  PyCodeObject *py_code = 0;
12875  PyFrameObject *py_frame = 0;
12876  PyThreadState *tstate = __Pyx_PyThreadState_Current;
12877  if (c_line) {
12878  c_line = __Pyx_CLineForTraceback(tstate, c_line);
12879  }
12880  py_code = __pyx_find_code_object(c_line ? -c_line : py_line);
12881  if (!py_code) {
12882  py_code = __Pyx_CreateCodeObjectForTraceback(
12883  funcname, c_line, py_line, filename);
12884  if (!py_code) goto bad;
12885  __pyx_insert_code_object(c_line ? -c_line : py_line, py_code);
12886  }
12887  py_frame = PyFrame_New(
12888  tstate, /*PyThreadState *tstate,*/
12889  py_code, /*PyCodeObject *code,*/
12890  __pyx_d, /*PyObject *globals,*/
12891  0 /*PyObject *locals*/
12892  );
12893  if (!py_frame) goto bad;
12894  __Pyx_PyFrame_SetLineNumber(py_frame, py_line);
12895  PyTraceBack_Here(py_frame);
12896 bad:
12897  Py_XDECREF(py_code);
12898  Py_XDECREF(py_frame);
12899 }

13022  static CYTHON_INLINE __pyx_t_float_complex __Pyx_c_pow_float(__pyx_t_float_complex a, __pyx_t_float_complex b) {
13023  __pyx_t_float_complex z;
13024  float r, lnr, theta, z_r, z_theta;
13025  if (b.imag == 0 && b.real == (int)b.real) {
13026  if (b.real < 0) {
13027  float denom = a.real * a.real + a.imag * a.imag;
13028  a.real = a.real / denom;
13029  a.imag = -a.imag / denom;
13030  b.real = -b.real;
13031  }
13032  switch ((int)b.real) {
13033  case 0:
13034  z.real = 1;
13035  z.imag = 0;
13036  return z;
13037  case 1:
13038  return a;
13039  case 2:

13046  z = __Pyx_c_prod_float(a, a);
13047  return __Pyx_c_prod_float(z, z);

13055  z.imag = 0;
13056  return z;
13057  } else if (a.real > 0) {
13058  r = a.real;
13059  theta = 0;
13060  } else {

13062  theta = atan2f(0, -1);
13063  }

13074  }

13202  return __Pyx_c_prod_double(z, z);
13203  }
13204  }
13205  if (a.imag == 0) {

13207  return a;
13208  } else if (b.imag == 0) {
13209  z.real = pow(a.real, b.real);
13210  z.imag = 0;
13211  return z;
13212  } else if (a.real > 0) {
13213  r = a.real;
13214  theta = 0;
13215  } else {
13216  r = -a.real;
13217  theta = atan2(0, -1);
13218  }
13219  } else {
13220  r = __Pyx_c_abs_double(a);
13221  theta = atan2(a.imag, a.real);
13222  }
13223  lnr = log(r);
13224  z_r = exp(lnr * b.real - theta * b.imag);
13225  z_theta = theta * b.real + lnr * b.imag;
13226  z.real = z_r * cos(z_theta);
13227  z.imag = z_r * sin(z_theta);
13228  return z;
13229  }
13230  #endif
13231 #endif
